title.narrative: Global Red Cross Network Text Message Campaigns

description.narrative: Since an estimated 80 percent of Haitians—even those living in the camps—have access to cell phones, the Red Cross has used this technology to rapidly deliver lifesaving messages related to health and disaster preparedness. The Red Cross has already delivered nearly 40 million text messages reaching at least 1.2 million people with messages that range from how to minimize risks during storms to how to identify, treat and prevent cholera. The Red Cross will continue to rely on this technology to rapidly disseminate critical information to Haitians.
